---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";

const sourceLinks = [
  { label: "Zippy's · About Us", href: "https://www.zippys.com/about-zippys" },
  { label: "Zippy's · Zipster Rewards", href: "https://www.zippys.com/zipster-rewards" },
  { label: "Max Holloway Foundation · Golf Classic", href: "https://maxhollowayfoundation.com/golf-tournament/" },
  { label: "Eater · Why Hawaiʻi Locals Love Zippy's", href: "https://www.eater.com/2019/2/25/18240255/zippys-hawaiis-favorite-fast-food-restaurant-video" },
];
---

<Base
  title="Growing Without Losing Home · Clark Hayashi"
  description="A solo, independent Zippy's mainland growth strategy and speculative campaign by Clark Hayashi."
>
  <article class="zippys-case" id="top">
    <div class="case-shell back-row">
      <a class="back-link" href="/work">← All work</a>
      <p>Solo project · Independent academic strategy</p>
    </div>

    <header class="case-shell hero">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Marketing strategy · Consumer insight · Speculative campaign</p>
        <h1>Growing Without Losing Home</h1>
        <p class="question">How can a local Hawaiʻi icon grow on the mainland without flattening what makes people love it?</p>
        <div class="meta-grid" aria-label="Project details">
          <div><span>Role</span><strong>Solo strategist and designer</strong></div>
          <div><span>Timeline</span><strong>2024 thesis · 2026 rebuild</strong></div>
          <div><span>Scope</span><strong>Research, strategy, campaign, measurement</strong></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="order-poster" aria-label="Speculative campaign poster">
        <span class="poster-label">Clark's usual</span>
        <strong>Korean Fried Chicken</strong>
        <i>+</i>
        <strong>Orange Bang</strong>
        <div class="poster-rule"></div>
        <p>The order that takes you home.</p>
        <small>Independent concept · not a Zippy's advertisement</small>
      </div>
    </header>

    <nav class="case-index" aria-label="Case study sections">
      <div class="case-shell">
        <a href="#starting-point">Starting point</a>
        <a href="#strategy">Strategy</a>
        <a href="#current-signal">Current signal</a>
        <a href="#campaign">Campaign</a>
        <a href="#measurement">Measurement</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <section class="personal-note">
      <div class="case-shell personal-grid">
        <p class="section-number">01 · Why this one</p>
        <blockquote>
          Zippy's is not an abstract brand to me. It is post-game meals, family orders, and knowing what everyone wants before the menu opens.
        </blockquote>
        <p class="usual-order">My usual:<br /><strong>Korean Fried Chicken<br />+ Orange Bang</strong></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-shell section-block" id="starting-point">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">The starting point</p>
        <h2>The original question was expansion. The better question was what must not be lost.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="two-column-copy">
        <div>
          <p class="lead">I completed the original strategy independently in 2024, then rebuilt it in 2026 as a sharper portfolio case study.</p>
          <p>The core tension still holds: Zippy's has recognizable products, digital ordering, and deep loyalty in Hawaiʻi. Mainland growth could create access for people who miss it and introduce the brand to new customers. It could also turn a specific local institution into a generic regional chain.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>This rebuild separates evidence from proposal. Public brand behavior informs the strategy; Seattle, the staged launch model, and the campaign are my recommendations, not claims about Zippy's plans.</p>
          <p>The goal is not to copy a Hawaiʻi restaurant elsewhere. It is to carry the relationship people have with the brand into a new market.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="thesis-band" id="strategy">
      <div class="case-shell">
        <p class="eyebrow light">The strategy</p>
        <h2>Earn the right to build the restaurant.</h2>
        <div class="strategy-grid">
          <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Start with Hawaiʻi-connected demand</h3>
            <p>Test where existing cultural familiarity can create the first repeat customers, not just launch-day attention.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Lead with orders and memories</h3>
            <p>Use real favorites and personal stories as the creative system. The menu becomes a way into the brand, not a list of products.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Scale only after repeat behavior</h3>
            <p>Move from waitlist to pop-up, retail test, delivery kitchen, and only then a permanent location.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-shell section-block market-section">
      <div class="section-heading split-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Recommended pilot</p>
          <h2>Seattle first. The West Coast remains the portfolio.</h2>
        </div>
        <p>This is a working market hypothesis, not a claim that Seattle has already been validated.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="market-card">
        <div><span>Market 01</span><strong>Seattle</strong></div>
        <p>Hawaiʻi ties, Asian and Pacific Islander food culture, direct travel, and a market I know personally make Seattle a strong place to learn before expanding farther.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Measure local waitlist concentration</li>
          <li>Run a weekend pop-up</li>
          <li>Track new-to-brand share and repeat intent</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <ol class="gate-line" aria-label="Stage-gated expansion model">
        <li><span>01</span><strong>Measure demand</strong><small>Waitlist, search interest, retail sales</small></li>
        <li><span>02</span><strong>Weekend pop-up</strong><small>Sell-through, order mix, new customers</small></li>
        <li><span>03</span><strong>Retail test</strong><small>Repeat purchase and household reach</small></li>
        <li><span>04</span><strong>Delivery kitchen</strong><small>Margin, radius, 30/60-day repeat</small></li>
        <li><span>05</span><strong>Permanent site</strong><small>Only after demand and operations clear the gate</small></li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="community-signal" id="current-signal">
      <div class="case-shell signal-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow light">A current signal · July 2026</p>
          <h2>Show up inside the community, not only in its ad feed.</h2>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>The first Max Holloway Golf Classic is scheduled for July 20, 2026, at Kapolei Golf Club. Its event page lists Zippy's in the sponsor group and schedules a named “Zippy's Breakfast and Warm-Up” at 9:00 a.m.</p>
          <p>That is strategically meaningful because the brand is participating through food, familiarity, and a local athlete. A mainland launch should preserve that instinct: join real community moments before asking the market for attention.</p>
          <a href="https://maxhollowayfoundation.com/golf-tournament/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View the event page ↗</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="campaign-section" id="campaign">
      <div class="case-shell">
        <p class="eyebrow light">Independent speculative campaign</p>
        <div class="campaign-heading">
          <h2>The Order That Takes You Home</h2>
          <p>A campaign platform built around usual orders, real memories, and measurable intent before Zippy's enters a new city.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="campaign-board">
          <article class="film-card">
            <span>30-second vertical film</span>
            <h3>One order. Three places in time.</h3>
            <p>A player walks off a Seattle court in the rain. A takeout bag lands on the passenger seat. The first bite cuts to family dinners back home. The order carries the story.</p>
            <strong>End card: What's the order that takes you home?</strong>
          </article>
          <article class="pop-card">
            <span>SEA · Weekend 01</span>
            <h3>What's the order that takes you home?</h3>
            <div class="ticket"><small>Clark's usual</small><strong>Korean Fried Chicken<br />+ Orange Bang</strong></div>
            <p>Join the market-test waitlist</p>
          </article>
        </div>

        <div class="campaign-system">
          <article><span>01</span><h3>Show Me Your Order</h3><p>Real stories from people with Hawaiʻi ties.</p></article>
          <article><span>02</span><h3>Five Orders, Five Stories</h3><p>Make menu range human and memorable.</p></article>
          <article><span>03</span><h3>My Usual</h3><p>Connect saved favorites to repeat behavior.</p></article>
          <article><span>04</span><h3>Seattle Weekend</h3><p>A pop-up designed to collect evidence.</p></article>
        </div>

        <p class="boundary"><strong>Creative boundary:</strong> Celebrity likeness is not used in the speculative advertising. The concept uses original characters; public videos and articles are research references only.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-shell section-block measurement-section" id="measurement">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">What success would mean</p>
        <h2>Attention is the opening metric, not the outcome.</h2>
      </div>
      <dl class="metric-list">
        <div><dt>Demand</dt><dd>Waitlist conversion · ZIP-code concentration · branded search lift</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Trial</dt><dd>Sell-through · new-to-brand share · order mix · average order value</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Retention</dt><dd>Rewards sign-ups · favorite saves · 30/60-day repeat</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Economics</dt><dd>Contribution margin · acquisition cost · delivery radius · waste</dd></div>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <section class="case-shell reflection">
      <p class="eyebrow">Reflection</p>
      <div>
        <h2>The rebuild made the recommendation more disciplined.</h2>
        <p>The 2024 work correctly focused on pop-ups, digital ordering, loyalty, Hawaiʻi-connected communities, and authentic storytellers. Revisiting it in 2026 forced me to choose one launch market, define gates, separate proof from hypothesis, and design measurement before media.</p>
        <p>The lesson I would carry into real client work: protect what people already love, then make every expansion step earn the next one.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sources-section">
      <div class="case-shell sources-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow light">Disclosure</p>
          <h2>Solo, independent strategy</h2>
          <p>I completed this project independently for academic and portfolio purposes. It was not commissioned by, affiliated with, endorsed by, or presented to Zippy's Restaurants.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="source-label">Selected public sources</p>
          <ul>
            {sourceLinks.map((source) => (
              <li><a href={source.href} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">{source.label} ↗</a></li>
            ))}
          </ul>
          <a class="top-link" href="#top">Back to top ↑</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .zippys-case {
    --z-paper: #f3eee3;
    --z-ink: #142521;
    --z-muted: #5f6965;
    --z-teal: #167979;
    --z-aqua: #9bd7d4;
    --z-orange: #ef6e31;
    --z-gold: #efb65a;
    --z-brown: #49362a;
    --z-line: rgba(20, 37, 33, 0.18);
    background: var(--z-paper);
    color: var(--z-ink);
  }

  .case-shell { width: min(1180px, calc(100% - 48px)); margin-inline: auto; }
  .back-row { min-height: 58px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--z-line); }
  .back-row p, .back-link { margin: 0; color: var(--z-muted); font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.07em; text-transform: uppercase; text-decoration: none; }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--z-ink); }
  .eyebrow, .section-number, .source-label { margin: 0 0 18px; color: var(--z-teal); font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 0.13em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .eyebrow.light { color: var(--z-aqua); }

  .hero { min-height: 760px; padding-block: clamp(64px, 9vw, 118px); display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.92fr) minmax(360px, 0.78fr); align-items: center; gap: clamp(48px, 8vw, 112px); }
  .hero h1, .section-heading h2, .thesis-band h2, .community-signal h2, .campaign-heading h2, .reflection h2, .sources-section h2 {
    margin: 0; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.055em; line-height: 0.93;
  }
  .hero h1 { max-width: 700px; font-size: clamp(4rem, 7vw, 7.2rem); }
  .question { max-width: 720px; margin: 34px 0 0; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 2.4vw, 2.2rem); line-height: 1.18; }
  .meta-grid { margin-top: 44px; padding-top: 20px; border-top: 1px solid var(--z-line); display: grid; gap: 14px; }
  .meta-grid div { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 110px 1fr; gap: 18px; }
  .meta-grid span { color: var(--z-muted); font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .meta-grid strong { font-size: 0.88rem; }

  .order-poster { min-height: 590px; padding: 30px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; background: linear-gradient(140deg, var(--z-orange), #f28a43 52%, var(--z-gold)); color: var(--z-brown); box-shadow: 18px 18px 0 var(--z-brown); }
  .order-poster::after { content: ""; position: absolute; inset: 0; background: repeating-linear-gradient(135deg, transparent 0 29px, rgba(73,54,42,.12) 30px 31px); pointer-events: none; }
  .order-poster > * { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .poster-label, .order-poster small { font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 0.11em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .order-poster strong { max-width: 460px; margin-top: 86px; font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 4.4vw, 4.6rem); line-height: 0.9; letter-spacing: -0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .order-poster strong + i { margin: 12px 0 -72px; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 2rem; }
  .order-poster i + strong { margin-top: 82px; }
  .poster-rule { width: 100%; flex: 1; min-height: 50px; margin: 28px 0 18px; border-bottom: 3px solid var(--z-brown); }
  .order-poster p { margin: 0 0 20px; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 3.3vw, 3.6rem); line-height: 0.95; }

  .case-index { position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 20; background: rgba(243,238,227,.94); border-block: 1px solid var(--z-line); backdrop-filter: blur(10px); }
  .case-index .case-shell { min-height: 58px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 28px; overflow-x: auto; }
  .case-index a { flex: 0 0 auto; color: var(--z-muted); font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: none; }
  .case-index a:hover { color: var(--z-teal); }

  .personal-note { padding-block: 40px; background: var(--z-ink); color: var(--z-paper); }
  .personal-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr 230px; gap: clamp(28px, 6vw, 76px); align-items: start; }
  .section-number { color: var(--z-aqua); }
  blockquote { margin: 0; max-width: 760px; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.4vw, 2.1rem); line-height: 1.25; }
  .usual-order { margin: 0; color: #c8d1ce; font-size: 0.84rem; }
  .usual-order strong { color: var(--z-paper); }

  .section-block { padding-block: clamp(90px, 11vw, 150px); }
  .section-heading { max-width: 980px; }
  .section-heading h2, .community-signal h2, .thesis-band h2, .reflection h2 { font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 5.2vw, 5.6rem); }
  .two-column-copy { margin-top: 60px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: clamp(44px, 8vw, 110px); }
  .two-column-copy p, .split-heading > p, .reflection p, .sources-section p { color: var(--z-muted); line-height: 1.75; }
  .two-column-copy p { margin: 0 0 18px; }
  .two-column-copy .lead { color: var(--z-ink); font-size: 1.15rem; }

  .thesis-band { padding-block: clamp(90px, 10vw, 138px); background: var(--z-brown); color: var(--z-paper); }
  .thesis-band h2 { max-width: 850px; }
  .strategy-grid { margin-top: 64px; border-block: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.3); display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
  .strategy-grid article { min-height: 330px; padding: 28px; border-right: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.3); }
  .strategy-grid article:last-child { border-right: 0; }
  .strategy-grid span { color: var(--z-gold); font-weight: 800; }
  .strategy-grid h3 { margin: 78px 0 14px; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.05; }
  .strategy-grid p { margin: 0; color: #ddd4c8; line-height: 1.65; }

  .split-heading { max-width: none; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 0.52fr; align-items: end; gap: 70px; }
  .split-heading > p { margin: 0; }
  .market-card { margin-top: 60px; padding: clamp(34px, 5vw, 62px); display: grid; grid-template-columns: 0.62fr 1fr 0.72fr; gap: 50px; align-items: center; background: var(--z-aqua); }
  .market-card div { display: grid; gap: 8px; }
  .market-card span { color: var(--z-teal); font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .market-card strong { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 4.5vw, 4.8rem); line-height: .95; }
  .market-card p { margin: 0; }
  .market-card ul { margin: 0; padding: 0; list-style: none; }
  .market-card li { padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(20,37,33,.24); font-size: .82rem; font-weight: 700; }
  .gate-line { margin: 44px 0 0; padding: 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr); list-style: none; border-block: 1px solid var(--z-line); }
  .gate-line li { min-height: 230px; padding: 24px 20px; border-right: 1px solid var(--z-line); display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .gate-line li:last-child { border-right: 0; }
  .gate-line span { color: var(--z-orange); font-size: .74rem; font-weight: 800; }
  .gate-line strong { margin-top: auto; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.35rem; line-height: 1.05; }
  .gate-line small { margin-top: 10px; color: var(--z-muted); line-height: 1.45; }

  .community-signal { padding-block: clamp(92px, 11vw, 150px); background: var(--z-teal); color: #f8f4eb; }
  .signal-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 0.9fr 1.1fr; gap: clamp(50px, 10vw, 140px); }
  .signal-grid p { margin: 0 0 20px; color: #d8e8e5; line-height: 1.75; }
  .signal-grid a { color: white; font-weight: 800; text-underline-offset: 4px; }

  .campaign-section { padding-block: clamp(90px, 11vw, 150px); background: var(--z-ink); color: var(--z-paper); }
  .campaign-heading { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.2fr .5fr; align-items: end; gap: 80px; }
  .campaign-heading h2 { font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 7vw, 7.5rem); }
  .campaign-heading p { margin: 0; color: #c6d0cc; }
  .campaign-board { margin-top: 70px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.18fr .82fr; border: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.3); }
  .campaign-board article { min-height: 510px; padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 62px); display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .campaign-board article > span { color: var(--z-aqua); font-size: .74rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .film-card h3, .pop-card h3 { margin: 44px 0 20px; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 4.8vw, 5.2rem); line-height: .94; }
  .film-card p { max-width: 650px; color: #c6d0cc; }
  .film-card strong { margin-top: auto; color: var(--z-gold); }
  .pop-card { background: var(--z-gold); color: var(--z-brown); }
  .pop-card > span { color: var(--z-brown) !important; }
  .pop-card h3 { margin-top: 52px; font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 4vw, 4.4rem); }
  .ticket { margin-top: auto; padding: 18px; display: grid; gap: 6px; background: var(--z-paper); border: 2px solid var(--z-brown); transform: rotate(-2deg); }
  .ticket small { color: var(--z-orange); font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .pop-card > p { margin: 28px 0 0; padding-top: 16px; border-top: 2px solid var(--z-brown); font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .campaign-system { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); border-left: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.3); }
  .campaign-system article { min-height: 250px; padding: 25px; border-right: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.3); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.3); }
  .campaign-system span { color: var(--z-orange); font-weight: 800; }
  .campaign-system h3 { margin: 56px 0 10px; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.45rem; }
  .campaign-system p { margin: 0; color: #aeb8b4; font-size: .85rem; }
  .boundary { margin: 40px 0 0; padding-block: 20px; border-block: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.3); color: #c6d0cc; }
  .boundary strong { color: var(--z-aqua); }

  .measurement-section { display: grid; grid-template-columns: .82fr 1.18fr; gap: clamp(60px, 10vw, 140px); }
  .metric-list { margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--z-line); }
  .metric-list div { padding: 22px 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr; gap: 30px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--z-line); }
  .metric-list dt { color: var(--z-orange); font-size: .76rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .metric-list dd { margin: 0; color: var(--z-muted); }

  .reflection { padding-block: clamp(90px, 11vw, 150px); display: grid; grid-template-columns: 170px 1fr; gap: clamp(50px, 9vw, 130px); border-top: 1px solid var(--z-line); }
  .reflection h2 { max-width: 900px; }
  .reflection p { max-width: 760px; }

  .sources-section { padding-block: clamp(78px, 9vw, 120px); background: var(--z-brown); color: var(--z-paper); }
  .sources-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr .8fr; gap: clamp(60px, 10vw, 150px); }
  .sources-section h2 { font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 5vw, 5rem); }
  .sources-section p { color: #ddd4c8; }
  .sources-section ul { margin: 0; padding: 0; list-style: none; border-top: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.3); }
  .sources-section li { border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.3); }
  .sources-section li a { display: block; padding: 15px 0; color: var(--z-paper); text-decoration: none; }
  .sources-section li a:hover { color: var(--z-aqua); }
  .top-link { display: inline-block; margin-top: 32px; color: var(--z-aqua); font-weight: 800; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero, .personal-grid, .two-column-copy, .split-heading, .market-card, .signal-grid, .campaign-heading, .measurement-section, .reflection, .sources-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero { min-height: auto; }
    .order-poster { min-height: 520px; }
    .personal-grid { gap: 22px; }
    .strategy-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .strategy-grid article { min-height: 260px; border-right: 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.3); }
    .strategy-grid article:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
    .strategy-grid h3 { margin-top: 54px; }
    .gate-line { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
